caption: Wow! Fantastic! Food was wonderful, large portions and of course, friendly staff! Marcos was a wonderful waiter and made the evening enjoyable! Thank you Victory! Additionally, great Covid protocols in place, we felt safe and clean!
Food was ok but overpriced . Our waiter was subpar . I don’t recommend it
Excellent food, great atmosphere, and an amazing wait staff. They have made great accommodations to keep customers safe during Covid.

Victory Italian never disappoints! Marcos is a top notch server, and the food is to die for. The calamari, burrata, and chicken Parmesan paired with their choice red wine made for a fantastic valentines date
Screwed up my order twice in a month!  Called them the 2nd time and was placed on hold for 10 minutes before they hung up the phone.  Not ordering again!

Amazing customer service and terrific meal! I had been looking for braciole for quite some time now, and saw that they were offering a Saturday special — just in time for my birthday. Unfortunately, the delivery apps that I was looking at didn’t have any of the updated specials — so I called over to the restaurant, and the most delightful person helped me find a workaround. Not only did the correct food get here (hot and on time), but they had included some wonderful birthday treats for me as well. Not only was the food fabulous, but the customer service was out of this world, especially during such a challenging time for restaurants. They’ve made some customers for life!

Great neighborhood Italian restaurant. We fell in love with Victory over the "quarantine summer," as they had a great outdoor setup. Now we've found ourselves ordering delivery from Victory almost every Friday. The food is absolutely delicious. A few highlights and go-to items: Grigliato Misto is a great appetizer, lots of fresh seafood. The brussel sprouts are amazing, we order those every time! Pizzas are all great, we especially love the Elmwood Park and the Arugala & Prosciutto. The meatballs and the sausage and peppers are phenomenal as well! My wife always gets the meatball salad or the eggplant stack for her entree, which both are always consistent and great. The pastas are all great (probably most notably, the Nonna's Gravy). Chicken dishes are all great, but the standout is the Chicken Saltimbocca, that is my new go-to order. As a bonus, they always include a slice of their garlic bread with each order, which is great.  On a side note, the delivery food is always very well-packed for travel and arrives hot. I can't say that about many restaurants consistently, but we have never had an issue with Victory delivery.  Overall, can't speak highly enough of Victory. And whenever we bring guests there, they always leave raving and plotting their next trip.  Can't wait to return in person
So good

Offers outdoor seating to safely social distance. We got the Fried Calamari for an appetizer. They were decently sized and delicious. Waitress recommended a great white wine that paired well with the food. My party loved their entrees. My only complaint is that the lasagna was a little bit salty.  Overall great experience!

Victory Italian is our favorite Italian restaurant in the neighborhood. The pork chops are my favorite, and my girlfriend loves their meatballs. They also have great drinks and excellent wine with a good atmosphere. Definitely recommend!
Incredibe meal!
An amazing restaurant. The presentation is spectacular and the staff is first class.
Love the people there. Good food. Bread for the table is delicious and their marinara is to die

THE BEST GARIC BREAD IN THE WORLD!!!  I could go and just eat the FREE garlic bread but everything we have eaten there has been good including the huge chicken parm and the awesome lasagna.  My fav Italian
Nice little neighborhood spot that’s much better than the trendy overpriced places you’ll find elsewhere downtown. Great food, great service, and wine that’s well-selected and fairly priced.
Nice food
The pizza is fantastic and the ribs on Sunday are delicious!! Service is excellent! Perfect neighborhood gem! Can't wait to return.
Great Italian selections

Just moved to the area & wanted some solid Italian take-out. Ordered Ceasar Salad & Shrimp Yvonne. Absolutely amazing!! The girls working up front were super nice & attentive. And the food...delish! Large portions, 2 meals for me. The shrimp were huge & cooked perfectly, generous sauce on pasta, complimentary garlic bread & crisp romaine for the salad. I'm so excited that this gem is around the block from me!!
During quarantine this has been the best hands down amazingly awesome setup/spread I've seen yet! Great brussels, pizza setups so cute and organized and delicious! Yessssss!
Great menu. Always good.
The veal marsala was VERY good. The rigatoni with vodka sauce with decent but I expected better. Was disappointed the pizza oven was broken. Overall, excited to try more dishes!

Excellent experience! Arrived with a reservation and was seated right away. Very good service, such nice people working there. The food was wonderful, and LARGE portions, we had to take so much home! Also they were very quick, we didn't get an appetizer, but we were in and out in 45 minutes. Such a great experience, we will be back for sure!

Everything was wonderful I just didn't like where we were seated next to the door and it was just very cold that night  so everytime  when the door opened it was a very nippy so we ate with are coats on.
Great food 👌 always fresh and hot🔥😍

Wow, I'm so impressed by the service and the food was phenomenal! The brick chicken was perfectly seasons and moist. The flavor of the chicken combined with the broccolini was the perfect pair. I cannot wait to go back!
Big portions, good service and the food was tasty.
Best Pizza In River North Area. Must try the Yardstick Pizza
Spectacular atmosphere with superb good and service. Very family friendly but also excellent for a date.

This place is fantastic. I haven't been in but have had delivered and the food is great. We ordered the wedge salad (huge butcher cut bacon), a pizza (best thing crust I've had) and the bacon agnolotti which was unique and delicious. Anyone who hasn't had a good experience should give it another shot!
Perfect room for a small party with delicious food!!
The ambience is warm and inviting; the staff is friendly and personable, and the food is delicious! I love this place and as a new Chicago I am so happy to have found a great Italian eatery to visit!
Food an service were outstanding
Great restaurant , really liked it here and the atmosphere was cool as well. I would definitely come back here again. I recommend this restaurant to everyone.

I’m an honest man. This place over books the amount of tables they can handle and lies to you about the amount of time you have before you are seated. This is a fact.  I have never gone out of my way to “sabotage” a restaurants reputation but when I was here I was lied to over and over about my reservation and when my family would be seated. We finally walked out after our reservation was over an hour past due.
Great! Loved this place and served!! Food was amazing and the staff was outstanding!  Definitely will go back!

Consistently delicious Italian food with great service and a great ambiance. So glad to have Victory in the neighborhood!  Make a reservation on weekends- it gets crowded!  The garlic bread which is complimentary is the best in the city. We had the Sicilian chopped salad which is huge and topped with a large shrimp and a breaded fried egg. Fabulous!  That was followed by the escarole and beans and the orchiette with sausage and rapini. So good!! The ambiance is warm and inviting- don’t miss this hidden jewel.
Amazing
Not the place for a quiet night out but that's ok. Food is good staple Italian nothing outstanding

The food was delicious, but what made this restaurant stand out was the service! Tony was our server - easily the best service we received during our visit to Chicago. We will be back for the chilli honey pepperoni pizza!
Yvonne the food is so great and good my God me and my family will be back keep up the great food

The perfect restaurant in River North. Finally a restaurant in River North that feels like a neighborhood restaurant! They are hard to fine and this place is it. The portions are enormous so don’t think the prices are like every other restaurant around. Two entrees for two people is plenty of food! The service is fantastic as well. Always a bonus when the manager comes around and asks how the meal is. We will definitely be coming back!

Definitely Italian comfort food. Delicious. Smooth sauce, easy to fall in love with it. Cozy place. Good service too. Reserved a table ahead, thankful we did, lots of people waiting for a table at 7:00 on a rainy weekend night.
Excellent service, worst fried chicken ever
Great people
Fantastic food, great service. Kayla was the best.
some of the best Italian food in Chicago.  Stuffed artichokes are incredible

We had a large group for a business dinner. Bobby warned us about the large portions and recommended “family style” so we wouldn’t throw food out. So glad he did. We were able to sample the sea bass, two different steaks, meatballs, calamari, pork chops, gnocchi, and brick chicken. All we were spectacular! They have a great wine list, inviting decor, and gold-medal service. Give them a try - you’ll be glad you did.
Best food in the city. Chef Joe is amazing !!

Look no further for excellent Italian food and service when you're in Chicago. This newish restaurant is sure to be a hit in the for many years to come. The lasagna was some of the best I've ever had, and the portions are HUGE (seriously...we didn't take our server's word for it and were surely mistaken). Speaking of service, hopefully you'll be lucky enough to get Tony. He as fantastic, very knowledgeable, and provided some of the best customer service we've ever had. The management was great and you can tell they take their business seriously.
Really delicious gnocchi and they always have treats for my dog.

Outstanding neighborhood Italian restaurant. Stumbled across this restaurant walking by and so glad I did. Certainly will be going back.  Service was impeccable and outstanding... thanks Tony! Food was really good, lots of flavor, quality ingredients, presentation was good. Vibe in the restaurant is really cool and nicely laid out with all the older photos on the walls
The service was top notch. Our server was very attentive and the food was excellent.  Recommend having a sicilian Manhattan if you happen to find yourself there. Definitely coming back!

By chance turned on to Ontario and discovered a fantastic place, seating outside on a beautiful Saturday afternoon (8/10), wait staff was a 10 as well as the food. Had the Chicken Marsala with extra shrooms and sauce, EXCELLENT !!!!
It's really bad not worth to spend $30 a plate

Where do I even start!? The location is prime yet low key. You can really enjoy a really well crafted meal with an excellent wine from their great selection. This is my second visit to Victory Italian, and I decided it was time to take my girlfriend to this gem. From the moment we arrived the staff was friendly and courteous. We were greated immediately and seated right away. The manager Jason came to welcome us to the restaurant.  The menu is vibrant and flavorful,  the more I saw the more hungry I got, but the garlic bread that was brought to the table helped me a bit to focus. We got a nice 2017 bottle of Daou which is a staple in my home, it just never disappoints.  On the calamari was spectacular! Fried to that perfect crisp golden brown and you can you tell it's going to be amazing by just looking at it. This fish is paired up with a really tasty cocktail sauce and a touch of horseradish. Now the main course was serious. My girlfriend went with the gnocchi with sausage and mushrooms, she did not speak to me the whole time we eat. The only thing she said if I recall correctly was "Oh. My. God.", until I decided to switch plates with her because I ordered Joe's Mama's Meatballs. BUT!! I asked our sever to substitute the tomato sauce for their Vodka sauce! (Who does that am I right?!) I'm so glad I did! I was already in disbelief of what i was tasting. Such a simple dish of spaghetti and meatballs in a vodka sauce, something I grew up eating all the time. But the flavor and the meatballs and the sauce and the wine, it was all perfect for me. When my girlfriend tried my dish she just went on and told me we needed to come back for my dish again. I didnt know I I almostvtisked not getting my plate back when I did that. Desserts were off the hook! Chef's Farina's tiramisu is a really great one, smooth clean, a classic. His cannoli was  a hit for both us, since my girlfriend and I are not big on cannolis,  I have to say this one may have changed my mind about them. 100/10 I will definitely will come back for more.

We went for ‘Yappy Hour’   ADORABLE outdoor patio. Not crowded.  Patrick, my server was delightful. They brought out this amazing bread-melted in my mouth.  I got the bacon pasta special. I can understand why it won the awards. Delicious!  Ill be back. Didn’t disappoint..
Delicious meal with huge portions!
Great Italian restaurant in the North Loop.  Quiet street.  Dine outside on the sidewalk or inside.  Patrick was outstanding!

The food is authentic and delicious. All the staff are so welcoming and accommodating. This is my favorite place to be. I feel like I’m eating with family and friends in my own home by how special they make every visit. Highly recommend!
Food and service were Great can't wait to go back again.
Amazing , love this place

I had their chilean seabass over spinach special and was very happy with the choice. My friends ordered pasta and it looked delicious. The server was very knowledgeable and very pleasant. I will def come back for more!

It's a very cosy place to hace a good beer  and  a good wine.
Great food and service!

Although Chicago is known for its Italian food scene, Victory Italian is able to deliver delicious food that is set aside by spectacular service. This is not the first "Victory" restaurant in Chicago which means that they know what they are doing. Our server, Pat, was attentive and energetic. Overall, the environment was enjoyable although our food took longer and the lasagna was rather dry. Despite these few bumps, the great service makes us eager to try this neighborhood spot again.

Do NOT, I repeat Do NOT ever order takeout here. The food is good, but the service is so bad. We have ordered takeout 5 times and they have screwed up our order once, completely lost the order twice, and been extremely late with another order.  They are severely understaffed at front of house and not trained properly. They have all these screens and papers everywhere and it’s just a jumbled mess. They frequently will answer the phone mid conversation with a customer and continue the conversation on the phone while customer is standing there.  It’s a shame because they are so close to us but we are done here. I’m sure the experience is much different if you dine in, but as far as take out I would run.
The atmosphere is great, workers are beyond friendly, and the food is awesome!
Great authentic Italian Restaurant with classy style of wine and cocktails. Nice ambience and reservations recommended.

In town for a hockey tournament, this was near the hotel. They did not disappoint. The garlic bread they start you off with may or may not be made with crack. It was absolutely incredible. The Chicken Parmesan was massive and cooked perfectly. The vodka sauce for the pasta was great. There were 10 of us including kids and the staff was welcoming and took great care of us. Portions were generous and drinks were strong. Will definitely come back.
Food is amazing!
Fantastic pasta and chicken!!  Great place!!
Classic old school Italian with Armands pizza, what more can I say.
Good food...their meatballs are great

Busy, vibrant, old-school place on the western edge of River North, this gem of a find for rustic Northern Italian classics was awesome from beginning to end. Being further from the theaters, it was full but not S-R-O, and we were able to get a table for two in just a few minutes. The  wine list should please most, with modest house selections and then reasonable prices for finer choices, leading to some rather top-shelf selections for those REALLY in the know.  Your first blessing is the amazing home-made slab/slice of garlic bread. They start with a 2" thick slice of focaccia, generously love it with butter and garlic, broil it to a fine balance of crisp and bronze, and finally give it a generous dressing of grated parmesan. What an opening!  Come hungry as the portions are nearly legendary; the lasagne is served in its own casserolette that easily can feed three adults (it was the perfect blend of spice, sauce, and cheeses-  offered in both meaty and vegetarian styles.)  So much to love  on the menu, we definitely will be back to try more when we next have the occasion to visit Chicago.   XO-
TJ was amazing, our evening was delightful.

I really enjoyed this place.  The food was outstanding, the service was great (particularly when you consider it was their third day open), the atmosphere is laid back, and the drinks are well priced.  My one negative comment is the music they played was a tad loud when I first sat down (Update: they completely fixed this.  This is an all around all star restaurant).  Otherwise, it was an overall great experience.

Party of 6 plus a baby for wife’s birthday dinner. Enjoyed the meatballs and calamari appetizers followed by house salad. Entree’s were all wonderfully prepared and extremely delicious. Portions were large instead of those overpriced small plates at RPM, Bar Sienna, etc. so most of took food home. Caesar,our waiter, was fun and knew the menu and all ingredients. Got the dessert sampler with a candle for the wife. Yum! We’re coming back!

This restaurant is as by far the best yet. The waiters are so hospitable. The food was amazing. Good quality and large portions. The Sicilian chopped salad was the best salad I ever had. Packed with delicious ingredients. Would recommend it. I can’t wait til my next visit is here
